The paper discusses the optimization of System-on-Chip (SoC) designs, which falls under the category of Embedded Systems (cs.ET). The paper also deals with data analysis and probabilistic modeling, which could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AR) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions software engineering (cs.SE) in the context of optimizing SoC designs. Finally, the paper discusses measures for detecting relationships between binary data, which could be categorized under Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it deals with data manipulation and analysis.
